[[File:DC_Grenade_Attachment.jpg|thumb|200px|The under-barrel grenade launcher used by [[Advanced Recon Commando/Legends|ARC troopers]] in the rescue of [[Ki-Adi-Mundi/Legends|Ki-Adi-Mundi]]]]
The '''under-barrel grenade launcher''', also known as an '''over-under''', was a special forces weapon designed as a miniature rocket/grenade launcher. The weapon could be attached to a modified version of the [[DC-15A blaster rifle/Legends|DC-15A blaster rifle]], [[DC-17m Interchangeable Weapon System/Legends|DC-17m Interchangeable Weapon System]], [[WESTAR-M5 blaster rifle]] or an [[E-15A blaster rifle]] via an [[Barrel/Legends|underbarrel]] attachment, and could be configured to fire a variety of other explosive projectiles.

[[Advanced Recon Commando/Legends|Advanced Recon Commandos]] put these weapons to use when rescuing [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Ki-Adi-Mundi/Legends|Ki-Adi-Mundi]] and several other [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] from [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]] on [[Hypori/Legends|Hypori]]. Although the salvo of grenades attacks did not significantly harm the incredibly agile Separatist general, they did manage to keep the [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]] preoccupied evading the explosive barrage.

[[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] also briefly used this weapon during his mission to [[Haruun Kal/Legends|Haruun Kal]].

[[Voort saBinring]] used a blaster rifle with an integrated under-barrel grenade launcher on missions to [[Chashima]] (in [[29 ABY/Legends|29 ABY]]) and [[Vandor-3]] (in [[44 ABY]]).

Specific examples of under-barrel grenade launchers include the [[Model MGL-1]], the [[Viper grenade launcher|Viper]] & the [[Viper 2 Grenade Launcher|Viper 2]], and the [[Under-Barrel HH-4|HH-4]].

